# Radioactivity from the radioactive ground

* [Reference](http://chemanalytica.com/book/novyy_spravochnik_khimika_i_tekhnologa/11_radioaktivnye_veshchestva_vrednye_veshchestva_gigienicheskie_normativy/5149)

Contribution of the thin spherical layer with activity $c$ ($\mathrm{Bq}/m^3$), gamma constant $K_{\gamma}$ ($\mathrm{Gr} m^2/(s \mathrm{Bq})$), distance from center $R$, thickness $dR$, coefficient of gamma-ray absorption $\mu$

$$d \dot{D} = \frac{e^{-\mu R} K_{\gamma} c 4\pi R^2 dR}{R^2}=4\pi c K_{\gamma} e^{-\mu R} dR $$.

Integrating we get $\dot{D} = 4\pi c K_{\gamma}/\mu$, for the activity inside the radioactive medium. We need to divide by 2 for half space filled with radioactive medium.

For $^{40}K$  $K_{\gamma}=5.05 10^{-18}\mathrm{Gr} m^2/(s \mathrm{Bq})$. Energy of $\gamma$-quantum is 1.46 MeV, probability of emission 0.106/Bq.

