# Radioactive household objects

* [Радиоактивные предметы в быту](http://www.ra4a.ru/forum/45-613-1)
    * K$_2$SO$_4$ 30 mkR/h
    * Granite  50 mkR/h
    * Uranium glass 100 mkR/h
    * Some vacuum tubes (direct heater type) $^232$Th
    * Wolfram welding electrodes WT-20 100 mkR/h
    * Thorium optics covering 1000 mkR/h
    * СПД (Светомассы постоянного действия) Radium based 1000-5000 mkR/h

* [Radioactive consumer products](http://www.orau.org/ptp/collection/consumer%20products/consumer.htm)
    * Fiesta dinnerware (uranium based glazing): 500-150000 mkR/h at surface
    * Uranium glass balls, etc.
    * Thorium lantern mantels (modern ones are based on Yttrium and are not radioactive)

* [Radioactivity in nature](http://www.physics.isu.edu/radinf/natural.htm)
    * Brazil nuts give about 1000-7000 pCi/kg of radium 1 pCi=36 Bq

